    <item>
      <title>Docker in dev containers</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/docker_in_dev_containers/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 10 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/docker_in_dev_containers/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Recently, I needed to use docker in a dev container for testing the docker build of &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/searxng/searxng/pull/4475&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;SearXNG&lt;/a&gt;. I was surprised to find that the Docker CLI was not running in the dev container. I had to do some digging to figure out how to get it running.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You can enable docker by adding the following to your &lt;code&gt;devcontainer.json&lt;/code&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;features&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;ghcr.io/devcontainers/features/docker-in-docker&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will use &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/devcontainers/features/tree/main/src/docker-in-docker&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;docker-in-docker&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/devcontainers/features&#34;  class=&#34;external-link&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;devcontainer/features&lt;/a&gt;. It will run another docker daemon from within the dev container. This means any child containers are completely independent of the host&amp;rsquo;s docker daemon. This can be useful for testing docker builds in a clean environment.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
